<span id="freeTextContainer14589758716688461820">The choice book that i am reading is titled, &quot;A Civil Action&quot; which is by the author, Jonathan Harr. This book is about a mystery case of the sickness that is going around infecting people in Woburn. The sickness case was revealed as Leukemia, which is Cancer, and some people are very concerned about this case. Some people think that the cause of the sickness is caused by the water from the wells in Woburn. There were resources that the water could turn out to be unsafe and uncleaned, especially</span>
  <span id="freeText14589758716688461820" style="display:none">The choice book that i am reading is titled, "A Civil Action" which is by the author, Jonathan Harr. This book is about a mystery case of the sickness that is going around infecting people in Woburn. The sickness case was revealed as Leukemia, which is Cancer, and some people are very concerned about this case. Some people think that the cause of the sickness is caused by the water from the wells in Woburn. There were resources that the water could turn out to be unsafe and uncleaned, especially with the smells in the water too, making it worse. so, the people of Woburn decided to make a case out of this situation, and they go to a very famous lawyer, Jan Schlichtmann, to help out with the problem</span>
