<div id="review_233206995" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/233206995" />
    <a title="Sarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/118210-sarah"><img alt="Sarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1375725168p2/118210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/233206995?book_show_action=true">Nov 08, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah" href="/user/show/118210-sarah">Sarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118210-sarah?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer233206995" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16153683871231741413">Well-paced and compelling for a non-fiction account of a mass tort action. I really felt for the unpolished young plaintiffs&apos; attorney and enjoyed reading about his rough practice-by-instinct, which is so different from the many layers of dilution that go into a junior lawyer&apos;s practice at a big firm. Given the unstoppable trajectory of the storytelling and the protagonist&apos;s huge, passionate efforts, I found the ending disappointing and lacking in denouement. Still a very good read. </span>
  <span id="freeText16153683871231741413" style="display:none">Well-paced and compelling for a non-fiction account of a mass tort action. I really felt for the unpolished young plaintiffs' attorney and enjoyed reading about his rough practice-by-instinct, which is so different from the many layers of dilution that go into a junior lawyer's practice at a big firm. Given the unstoppable trajectory of the storytelling and the protagonist's huge, passionate efforts, I found the ending disappointing and lacking in denouement. Still a very good read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16153683871231741413" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


